If you're still searching for the perfect snack, this is an episode you're going to LOVE.

My guest and I do a deep dive on pili nuts - one of the healthiest nuts on the planet - and one of my personal favorites!

You'll hear from Jason Thomas, the founder of @pilihunters, a sustainable food company aiming to reshape the food industry one nut at a time.

Jason shares how he built an incredibly successful company with just 15 pounds of deep-fried pili nuts and a dream. We also discuss the benefits of #pilinuts - and how having just a handful a day could support your health.

On this episode you'll learn:

✳️ Why eating fat does NOT make you fat (and the real culprit behind stubborn weight gain) (5:00)
✳️The essential mineral most Americans are missing on their diet (and how it can support heart and muscle function) (8:20)
✳️The difference between organic and wild foods (and which is better)(10:20)
✳️How to feel full for HOURS on end (without consuming a ton of food or calories) (11:00)
✳️The world's healthiest fermented honey (and how it may help break down lectins in your body) (41:30)
✳️The delicious and unique ways you cab incorporate pili nuts into your diet for better health and a slimmer physique 33:50)

**Customer spotlight**

Pili Hunters is stoked to be part of @runsmilebreathe's active lifestyle. Eric is a multisport explorer and an amazing photographer. We are glad to fuel his badass trainings across the country. Let's wish him luck on his upcoming race, the beastly Badwater 146💪

"For me, Pili hunters ignites passion. Passion of movement in the mountains. Whether it be guiding on Denali at high elevation, to fueling my runs across Death Valley in summer, Pili enables me to perform at my highest level with sustained energy.

Pili Hunters products, such as my favorite Maca and Cacao Pili nut butter and Dark Chocolate bar delivers nutrient density and combines quality high fats and minimal superfood ingredients, which is unparalleled in its field. 

Combine the truly delicious, unique buttery taste of the Pili nut with the sustainability, cultural integration of the farmers and the rich volcanic soil where the Pili trees grow, I’m grateful to include Pili in my “micro-ventures”…every. single. day."

Why are Pili Hunters spouted pili nuts better? 

Nuts and seeds contain phytic acid, which is considered an anti-nutrient because it blocks iron, zinc, and calcium absorption, which can result in mineral deficiencies. 

Pili Hunters pili nuts have removed the phytic acid containing layer, leaving minerals and nutrients readily available for your body to absorb. Sprouted pili nuts are also soft and buttery, which is perfect for those who might avoid hard nuts for fear of cracking a tooth. 👏

KETO CEREAL 🥣 

When starting a low carb/ Keto lifestyle, finding substitutes can be challenging. A big breakfast favourite is cereal so I wanted to create a no sugar added, low carb cereal that still tasted delicious. And guess what? This recipe is also dairy-free and vegan too 🎉

Wondering what Muesli is? Muesli is generally a mix of oats, nuts, and seeds. However, to keep things low carb, I removed the oats but kept all the Keto friendly ingredients like almonds, pumpkin seeds, and pili nuts. This is a great meal idea for diabetics as well since there is no sugar!

Servings: 6 | Prep time: 15 minutes | Total time: 30 minutes Ingredients:
Muesli Cereal
1 cup sunflower seeds
1/2 cup sliced almonds 
1/2 cup pumpkin seeds
1/4 cup raw pecans (chopped)
1/4 cup @pilihunters Pili Nuts (chopped)
1/2 cup unsweetened coconut flakes 
1/2 tsp @originvanilla Salt
1/2 tsp @burlapandbarrel Royal Cinnamon
1/2 tbsp granular sweetener (optional)

Other Ingredients
1/2 @ketobars Chocolate Coconut (chopped) 
1/2 cup @addjoi Almond Milk (prepared)
30g raspberries

Directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 350F
2. In a large bowl, mix all muesli ingredients together
3. On a baking sheet, distribute muesli ingredients and toast for 10-12 minutes
4. Remove from the oven and let cool
5. Pour 1 serving of cereal into a small bowl and add Keto Bar and raspberries
6. Pour 1⁄2 cup of JOI Almond milk over top and enjoy!
